<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,152,1187]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1125,1151]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is Latin, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilkamaa &amp; Halenius &amp; Ševčík" authorityYear="2019" box="[561,653,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Pseudoaerumnosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosa">
<emphasis box="[561,653,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">formosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, beautiful, referring to the elegant curvature of the apical tooth of the gonostylus.
</paragraph>
